main event: Objects were seen oscillating in the sky over Southern California from Los Angeles to San Diego on 29 June 1956.
interesting points: The sighting lasted approximately 2 hours and involved objects that appeared silvery-white,The objects oscillated as the sun set, making observations more challenging,The sighting was reported by multiple observers, including the police department in Ontario, California,Two F3D aircraft were scrambled but could not reach the altitude of the objects,The investigation concluded that the sighting was likely caused by a balloon, which was common in the area at the time.
witness description: numerous observers located in Redlands, San Bernardino, and Ontario, California
